doc.after: In the 19th century, most emigration from Malta was to North Africa and the Middle East, although rates of return migration to Malta were high.[157] Nonetheless, Maltese communities formed in these regions. By 1900, for example, British consular estimates suggest that there were 15,326 Maltese in Tunisia, and in 1903 it was claimed that 15,000 people of Maltese origin were living in Algeria.[158]
